  "text": "Accurate segmentation is important for clinical interpretation. In diseased eyes, pathologies such as drusen, intraretinal cysts, edema, or subretinal fluid can make automated segmentation less robust. Although significant improvements have been made, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] expert manual correction is sometimes necessary. Software that aids or reduces the workload required for manual correction of volumetric data is beneficial.",
